A mass funeral for the victims of the Enyobeni Tavern tragedy is underway on Wednesday, 6 July. Follow our live blog below for up-to-date reporting. The funeral for the 21, who died in June, will be held on the Scenery Park Sports Ground in East London.     President Cyril Ramaphosa will be in attendance to honour the victims, as will Eastern Cape Premier Oscar Mabuyane and Police Minister Bheki Cele.  Updates will appear below. Please refresh the tab if required.  During a visit to Gugulethu, Cape Town on Tuesday, Cele said investigating officers “are making headway into their investigations”.  He said “better responses” and a full briefing will be made available on Wednesday.  “We want to make sure something like this never happens again. It’s a sad situation, and it’s a situation that breaks every human being that has a soul,” Cele said.  ALSO READ: Enyobeni tavern: SA in need of a serious conversation about underage drinking Meanwhile, Police Minister Bheki Cele had to excuse himself from a live interview as he broke down in tears.  Cele later said: “It’s a terrible scene. They are pretty young. When you are told they are 13 years, 14 years and you go there, and you see them. It breaks [you].” NOW READ: Enyobeni Tavern: Saps investigating liquor legislation compliance